Former Somalia president Ali Mahdi Muhammad has died at a Nairobi hospital after being hospitalised with Covid-19. Somalia Information ministry spokesperson Ismael Omar confirmed the death. Muhammad served as the President of Somalia from January 1991 to January 1997. He was opposed by Gen Aidid and re-elected during a conference in Djibouti in July 1991. He was nominally president until the election of Abdiqasim Salad in August 2000. Mahdi was born in Addow Uul, Middle Shabelle.